result.execSummary:
The defendant Kevin M. Tetzlaff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Tetzlaff appeared in court, in custody, Attorney John Charles Bachman appeared in court for Kevin M. Tetzlaff, Attorney Peter J. Rindal appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. Victim/Witness statute complied with. 
Defendant enters a no contest plea to:
21CF1190: 
Count 1: 2nd Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety as a Repeater
Count 2: Attempting to Flee or Elude an Officer as a Repeater
Count 5: Identity Theft as a Party to a Crime and as a Repeater
Count 8: Carrying a Concealed Knife as a Repeater

22CF8
Count 1: Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude an Officer as a Repeater
Count 2: 2nd Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, as a Repeater

Priors as related to these charges are acknowledged. 
21TR8913 - Speeding 45 mph over
21TR8912 - Failure to Keep Vehicle Under Control

Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Court accepts plea and finds the defendant guilty. Anything else in these files and all other citations are ordered dismissed and read in.

AODA and follow through with recommendations.

No contact with S.H., G.G., or B.S.
court costs

Court orders on misdemeanor count (Count 8 in 21CF1190):
court costs and DNA sample and surcharge

Court orders: 21TR8913 - $213.10 forfeiture and 21TR8912 - $515.50 forfeiture

Conditions:
Defendant not to drive without a valid driver's license.
Defendant to maintain absolute sobriety.
Comply with Pre-Trial Monitoring Services.
